    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>02600701700014</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>This expression here probably means "to run with water" | the image is of urine running down the knees, because of fear (cf. Greenberg loc.cit.). There has also been a suggestion that בִרְכַּיִם here means penis or the male genitalia | in this case we would have an extended meaning within the same lexical domain, and a contextual domain Liquids | Confidence.</Content>
    </Note>
